## Working Features

- Gazebo launches warehouse world correctly
- AGV spawns once at home dock (0, 0, yaw=90deg)
- No double-spawn or teleportation
- Diff-drive plugin publishes odom at 50Hz
- Odom frame = world frame (no transform needed)
- TF tree: odom -> base_footprint -> base_link
- 8-channel virtual line sensor detects guide tape
- PID line follower tracks spine and aisles
- IMU-based turn controller (90deg and 180deg turns)
- RFID tag detection with arm/disarm logic
- Mission FSM: IDLE -> NAV_SPINE -> TURNING -> NAV_AISLE -> AT_SHELF -> PICKUP -> PIVOT -> RET_AISLE -> RET_TURN -> RET_SPINE -> DOCKED
- Junction counting for aisle selection
- Return-to-home with correct LEFT turn at spine junction
- E-Stop and Reset via topics
- Reset-to-dock via `/atlas/reset_to_dock` (calls Gazebo set_entity_state)
- CLI mission sender: `ros2 run atlas_mission_manager send_mission S05`
- RViz config with robot model, TF, odometry display

